Questionnaire model: In classifier-constrained methods, we trained a CNN for each of the nine symptom classifiers. We used filters of sizes {{2204.10432_FO0025||FO}}, and one filter for each size. Consequently, the max-pooling produces a vector of size {{2204.10432_FO0026||FO}}, which is then fed into the final linear layer for prediction. We apply {{2204.10432_FO0027||FO}} regularization specifically to the CNN kernels. The {{2204.10432_FO0028||FO}} weights were fine-tuned with three options [{{2204.10432_FO0029||FO}}, {{2204.10432_FO0030||FO}}, {{2204.10432_FO0031||FO}}].